items.name: Children's Books Wiki
items.title: Children's Books Wiki
items.headline: Children's Books Wiki
items.desc: Children's Books Wiki is a freely editable database about books written for children ages 0-16, and the young at heart. Each book has a description, readers' reviews, guidance on content, recommended reading age and suggestions for what to read next. Come and visit the only collaborative website dedicated to children's books!

items.name: Married with Children Wiki
items.title: Married with Children Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Married With Children Wiki
items.desc:
Married... with Children ran for eleven seasons, totaling 262 episodes and airing from April 5, 1987 to June 9, 1997. The series was also renown for it's handling of topic and subject matter that were at the time, considered non-standard which earned it both praise and criticism.

The show followed the lives of Al Bundy (Ed O'Neill), a once-glorious high school football player turned hard-luck salesman of women's shoes, and his family.

items.name: Children's Film Festival Wiki
items.title: Children's Film Festival Wiki
items.headline: Family Fun at the Bay Area International Children's Film Festival
items.desc:
If you're looking for a weekend cultural event in the San Francisco Bay Area that's stimulating for children and relaxing for parents, you've come to the right place!

The 5th Annual Bay Area International Children's Film Festival, a Playdate for the Imagination, is set for SATURDAY, JANUARY 26 & SUNDAY, JANUARY 27, 2013, at the beautiful art deco theater, Michaan's Auctions, in Alameda, California.

Doors open at 9am. Starting at 10:00am, we'll screen a series of shorts for all ages and a feature film for ages 6 and up. Starting at 1:30pm, we'll show a series of shorts and a feature film for ages 9 and up. Children age 3 and under are free.

items.name: Child of Light Wiki
items.title: Child of Light Wiki
items.headline: Get Lost in the Child of Light Wikia!
items.desc: Child of Light is an upcoming 2D Adventure/RPG/Puzzle game developed and published by Ubisoft. Child of Light centers around Aurora, the daughter of a duke from 1895 Austria, who contracts a physical ailment that causes her to fall asleep. Upon waking up, she finds herself wound up in the mythical world of Lemuria, which has had its sun, moon and stars stolen by the Black Queen. Aurora is entrusted with the task to defeat the mad Queen and recover the celestial bodies to ultimately reuinite with her father. In her journey she is accompanied by Igniculus, a helpful pyrefly who can be controlled by a second player.

items.name: Children Of Morta Wiki
items.title: Children Of Morta Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Children of the Morta wikia!
items.desc:
Recently funded at Kickstarter, Children of Morta is described as a hack-n-slash roguelike adventure game starring the Bergson family. For years the Bergsons enjoyed a peacful life, the parents rasing their children to become Guardians. One day, their peaceful god is gone, corruption comes to the mountain and life as they knew it has changed. Anxious to find out what happened, the Bergson family set off on an adventure deep into the mountain, encountering many dangers along the way. Join the family as they seek the seeds of life to use against the corruption and face the unknown perils of their journey. Players will be able to play as any of the family members , each with their own special abilites, emotions and struggles. 
The wiki is community edited and maintained. Anyone can contribute and we hope to have you join us and help fill in the wikia as launch gets closer and we know more about the game!
